Fix apex hostname for cr3/ddclient PR #876 (Hetzner Cloud DNS).

PR #876 computes the rrset name with:
    (my $hostname = $domain) =~ s/\Q.$zone\E$//;
which requires a leading dot, so when domain equals zone (the apex) the
substitution does not happen and ddclient sends the full FQDN as the rrset
name. Hetzner accepts that as a relative name, producing a bogus rrset that
becomes "homefree.host.homefree.host" when fully qualified, while the real
apex ("@") is never touched.

Force "@" when domain equals zone.

--- a/ddclient.in
+++ b/ddclient.in
@@ -6035,6 +6035,7 @@
 
         my $zone = opt('zone', $domain);
         (my $hostname = $domain) =~ s/\Q.$zone\E$//;
+        $hostname = '@' if $hostname eq $zone;
         my $ipv4 = delete $config{$domain}{'wantipv4'};
         my $ipv6 = delete $config{$domain}{'wantipv6'};
